<TITLE> Prof Shah named KU VC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Khulna, Oct 14 (bdnews24.com) Acting vice chancellor M Saifuddin Shah has been appointed to the top job at the Khulna University for four years, the education ministry said Tuesday. A professor of fisheries and marine technology, Shah took over temporarily on Feb 28 after professor Mahbubur Rahman resigned. On Sept 12, a government search committee recommended three names including Shah. Meanwhile, the committee has named VC panels for three other public universitiesBangladesh Agricultural University in Mymensingh, Patuakhali Science and Technology University and Noakhali Science and Technology University. The decisions came from a committee meeting on Tuesday, ministry spokesman Subodh Chandra Dhali told bdnwes24.com. bdne
